nabis dealing and drug use, violence, masculinity, hip-hop culture, experiences with the welfare system, and issues of immigration and racism. The book also analyses the discursive practice of marginalised people on the street and identifies the narratives by which these young men live.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCannabisxSocial aspects. 0aCrimezNorwayzOslo. 0aDrug dealerszNorway. 0aDrug trafficzNorway. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aPedersen, Willy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978184742901840uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847421753?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847421753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847421753/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles